cher in [$\\alpha$/Fe] than\nthe younger ones. We could estimate the abundance [$\\alpha$/Fe]=0.14 dex as the\nboundery separating the $\\alpha$-rich and $\\alpha$-poor sub-samples in the\n[$\\alpha$/Fe]$\\times$[Fe/H] plane.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Sep 2019 08:41:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-13"}
